articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A surface-to-surface missile fired at central Israel from Yemen hit an unpopulated area, causing no injuries, Israel's military said on Sunday.
articles.title: Missile fired from Yemen set off sirens in central Israel, military says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: At least 30 people, including three children, were injured when a Russian guided bomb hit a high-rise residential building in Kharkiv in northeastern Ukraine on Sunday.
articles.title: Russian bomb injures at least 30 civilians in Ukraine's Kharkiv, officials say

articles.author: David W Cerny, Marek Strzelecki
articles.description: One person drowned in southwest Poland and thousands were evacuated across the border in the Czech Republic after heavy rain continued to batter central Europe on Sunday, causing flooding in several parts of the region.
articles.title: Floods claim two more casualties as torrential rain batters central Europe

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Jordan's Prime Minister Bisher Khasawneh submitted his resignation on Sunday, officials familiar with the matter said, less than week after a parliamentary election that saw some gains for the Islamist opposition in the U.S.-allied kingdom.
articles.title: Jordan prime minister submits resignation days after election, sources say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Georgia's most powerful man, Bidzina Ivanishvili, suggested that the South Caucasus country could apologise to Ossetians for the 2008 war with Russia that led to Moscow recognising two rebel Georgian regions, Georgian media reported.
articles.title: Georgia's most powerful man suggests an apology for 2008 war with Russia

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ukrainian troops are suffering high losses because Western arms are arriving too slowly to equip the armed forces properly, President Volodymyr Zelenskiy told CNN in an interview aired on Sunday.
articles.title: Ukraine suffering high losses due to slow arms supplies, says Zelenskiy

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Indian opposition leader Arvind Kejriwal said on Sunday he will resign as chief minister of the Delhi regional government, a day after he was released from prison on bail in a graft case.
articles.title: Released Indian opposition leader Kejriwal to resign as Delhi chief minister

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Eight people have died trying to cross the Channel from France to England, French authorities said on Sunday, confirming earlier media reports.
articles.title: Eight die in Channel crossing attempt, French authorities say

articles.author: Ruma Paul
articles.description: The United States is committed to supporting Bangladesh's inclusive economic growth, institution building and development and will provide an additional $202 million of aid, a U.S. delegation said during a visit to Dhaka on Sunday.
articles.title: US to give Bangladesh $202 million more in aid

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ecuador will implement a nationwide blackout for maintenance in the country's electricity system overnight on Wednesday, from 10 p.m. local time to Thursday at 6 a.m., the government said in a statement on Sunday.
articles.title: Ecuador to implement nationwide blackout overnight on Wednesday
